  "detailedRequirements": "<p><em>This challenge is part of Project SERENITY: a refresh of the topcoder challenge lifecycle. There are many challenges before it and will be many after it but you should be able to clone this repo: https://github.com/topcoderinc/serenity-core, grok the README and be up to speed in a few minutes. &nbsp; This project pulls heavily from the MEAN.io stack but with PostgreSQL support.</em></p>\n\n<p>I ran a challenge a few weeks ago called <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/challenge-details/30045580/?type=develop\">Markdown and up again</a>&nbsp;and we got some great submssions. &nbsp; However some things have changed since how we are planning on using this so I wanted to re-run this to get a much simple directive.</p>\n\n<p>The original submission allowed the user to &nbsp;select if they were authoring the text in markdown or html via a radio button which stores the selection in the payload whose field type is JSON. &nbsp; We love this submission but here are the changes that we need to be made: &nbsp;1.) We are only allowing the users to use Mardown! &nbsp;no HTML. &nbsp; 2.) we want the preview to display in in the same div (not really one is hidden) that the user is editing aka github style. &nbsp; Since we are only support Markdown we don&rsquo;t have the need to change the field type to JSON, thus allowing us to not modify our schema.</p>\n\n<p>1. &nbsp;Use the attached Mardown and up again as a starting point or you may choose to start from scratch.<br />\n2. &nbsp;Modify the directive to only use markdown and rename the directive tc-markdown.<br />\n3. &nbsp;Above the textbox add two links: preview and markdown help<br />\n4. &nbsp;When the user clicks preview the text area should be hidden and the markdown preview should takes in place and the &lsquo;preview&rsquo; link changes to &lsquo;edit&rsquo;. &nbsp; When the user click edit it switches back to the edit mode.&nbsp;<br />\n5. &nbsp;Apply your directive to the article.content edit/create and the challenge.description edit/create page.<br />\n6. &nbsp;An ideal solution will not require the field types to change from their default TEXT, STRING or CHAR types.<br />\n7. &nbsp;The included submission took the liberty of refactoring the edit/create with a checknew() method to only use the edit view but this is not necessary since create and edit will eventually contain different options.<br />\n8. &nbsp;Be sure to pull the latest source from the repo above.</p>\n",
